I could not find a way to do it so I guess it's a feature request.

I have several tasks
1. build 1: tsc build project 1
2. build 2: tsc build project 2 (dependent on project 1)
3. styles: node-sass
4. clear: solution (deletes some files)

I wanted to create new task to do clean build of all. So I created new task using `dependsOn`
Problem is that new task is running all children in parallel with no dependencies which obviously does not work for me.

Proposal, change property `dependsOn` in following way:

```json
    "dependsOn": {
        "tasks": ["clear"],
        "then": {
            "tasks": [
                {
                    "tasks": ["build 1"],
                    "then": {
                        "tasks": ["build 2"]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "tasks": ["styles"]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
```
all tasks in `tasks` array at given level can be executed in parallel, after finishing go to `then` and proceed.

interface:

```ts
interface ITask {
    tasks: (ITask | string)[];
    then?: ITask;
}
```

Alternatively you could just add new property `subTask` - pointing to task that needs to be build before.
I would be enough to get dependencies, simpler to implement - but it would require to create a lot of fake tasks.

Version 1.15.1

